TY  - JOUR
T1  - Social Capital in Multinational Corporations and a Micro-Macro Model of its Formation
AU  - Kostova, Tatiana
AU  - Roth, Kendall
Y1  - 2003/04/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2003.9416356
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2003.9416356
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 297
EP  - 317
VL  - 28
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Linking theories of social capital with theories of multinational corporations (MNCs), we discuss the need for and creation of social capital in foreign subunits of MNCs. We argue that the required levels and forms of social capital are determined by the nature of interdependence between headquarters and subunits, and thus vary by different models of MNCs. We then develop a micro-macro model of social capital formation, explaining how boundary spanners form their private social capital and how this social capital is transformed into public social capital of the subunit.
AB  - Linking theories of social capital with theories of multinational corporations (MNCs), we discuss the need for and creation of social capital in foreign subunits of MNCs. We argue that the required levels and forms of social capital are determined by the nature of interdependence between headquarters and subunits, and thus vary by different models of MNCs. We then develop a micro-macro model of social capital formation, explaining how boundary spanners form their private social capital and how this social capital is transformed into public social capital of the subunit.
