TY  - JOUR
T1  - Learning from Business Failure: Propositions of Grief Recovery for the Self-Employed
AU  - Shepherd, Dean A.
Y1  - 2003/04/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2003.9416377
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2003.9416377
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 318
EP  - 328
VL  - 28
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this paper I use the psychological literature on grief to explore the emotion of business failure, suggesting that the loss of a business from failure can cause the self-employed to feel grief?a negative emotional response interfering with the ability to learn from the events surrounding that loss. I discuss how a dual process of grief recovery maximizes the learning from business failure.
AB  - In this paper I use the psychological literature on grief to explore the emotion of business failure, suggesting that the loss of a business from failure can cause the self-employed to feel grief?a negative emotional response interfering with the ability to learn from the events surrounding that loss. I discuss how a dual process of grief recovery maximizes the learning from business failure.
