TY  - JOUR
T1  - When Will Stakeholder Groups Act? An Interest- and Identity-Based Model of Stakeholder Group Mobilization
AU  - Rowley, Timothy I.
AU  - Moldoveanu, Mihnea
Y1  - 2003/04/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2003.9416080
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2003.9416080
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 204
EP  - 219
VL  - 28
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Using social movement and social identity theories, we construct a model of stakeholder group action that challenges the current notion that interests drive stakeholder group action. We argue that interests do not easily translate into action, mobilization can be motivated by a desire to express an identity as well as protect interests, and overlapping (similar) memberships across multiple stakeholder groups affect stakeholder group action. As a result, we develop several propositions based on our elaboration of interest-based action and inclusion of identity-based action.
AB  - Using social movement and social identity theories, we construct a model of stakeholder group action that challenges the current notion that interests drive stakeholder group action. We argue that interests do not easily translate into action, mobilization can be motivated by a desire to express an identity as well as protect interests, and overlapping (similar) memberships across multiple stakeholder groups affect stakeholder group action. As a result, we develop several propositions based on our elaboration of interest-based action and inclusion of identity-based action.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2003.9416080
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2003.9416080
Y2  - 2026/04/24
